cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper deals with convergence guarantees and optimization techniques for modern convolutional neural networks, which are primarily used in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of adaptive optimizers such as RMSProp and Adam, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS) applications.
